why CSS selector used in HTML?

Css selector is used to select HTML element which you want to style such as alignment, color,font-size,font-family etc.
With the help of it, we can easily style the HTML elements.

FOR EXAMPLE::
                <!DOCTYPE html>
                <html>
                    <head>
                          <style>
                                p {
                                  text-align: center;
                                  color: red;
                                } 
                          </style>
                    </head>
                    <body>

                          <p>CSS SELECTOR</p>
                          <p id="para1">USE OF CSS SELECTOR</p>

                    </body>
                </html>

OUTPUT:: Text display in center with red color.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are different type of selector?

 Their are 5 types of CSS selectors:

Simple selectors : It select elements based on name, id, class.
Combinator selectors : It select elements based on a specific relationship between them.
Pseudo-class selectors : It select elements based on a certain state.
Pseudo-elements selectors : It select and style a part of an element.
Attribute selectors : It select elements based on an attribute or attribute value.

=>CLASS SELECTOR
The class selector uses the class attribute of an HTML element to select a specific element to give style.
=>ID SELECTOR
The id selector uses the id attribute of an HTML element to select a specific element to give style.
            FOR EXAMPLE::
                <!DOCTYPE html>
                <html>
                    <head>
                          <style>
                               #para1{
                                  text-align: center;
                                  color: red;
                                } 
                               .para2{
                                   color:green;
                                }
                          </style>
                    </head>
                    <body>

                          <p class="para2">CSS SELECTOR</p>
                          <p id="para1">USE OF CSS SELECTOR</p>

                    </body>
                </html>

=>The universal selector (*) selects all HTML elements on the page.
=>Grouping selector is used to give similar style to the different HTML element. 

                                                <html>
                                                     <head>
                                                          <style>
                                                          h1, h2, p {
                                                            text-align: center;
                                                            color: red;
                                                          }
                                                          </style>
                                                     </head>
                                                     <body>

                                                          <h1>Hello World!</h1>
                                                          <h2>Smaller heading!</h2>
                                                          <p>This is a paragraph.</p>

                                                     </body>
                                                </html>

